title: Walking Dead fans spot object flying in latest episode | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share One user wrote: 'Anyone else see the plane flying behind Rick after he killed the beast? #TheWalkingDead #TalkingDead' How random: When the moment happened, Twitter users were quick to write about it Could it be? More fans noticed that thing behind Rick's head soar by A defeated purpose? One fan pointed out that if a plane went by, then the characters should be able to have access for flight Conspicuous: Some viewers aren't sure if that possible plane was a mistake or intentional Another wrote: 'You guys had a plane in this episode did you know that?' Whether it was a mistake or intentional, no one from the show has said anything about it yet. As for how things went in the most recent episode, Daryl and Carol reunited, but it came with a difficult choice for Daryl on what's been happening with Negan. While Negan has been killing people, Daryl decided to lie to Carol about it; Norman Reedus (Daryl), 48, spoke to Entertainment Weekly on why his character did this. Reunited: The episode had a big moment when Daryl (Norman Reedus) visited Carol (Melissa McBride) to talk to her about Negan (Jeffrey Dean Morgan) 'She needs to hear that,' Norman said. 'She's going through her own thing and there's a reason why she separated herself and doesn't want to be a killer anymore.' 'And she's losing herself, and I think Daryl realizes that. It's a very selfless act.' 'He tells her what she needs to hear to keep going. He does it for her.' 'He wants revenge:' The actor told Entertainment Weekly that his character is thirsty for vengeance and 'wants to kill people' The actor also revealed what's next for his character. 'He wants revenge,' Norman said. 'He's got tunnel vision right now. He wants to kill people.' The Walking Dead airs on Sundays at 9 p.m. ET on AMC. Read more: Share or comment on this article 148
